
HOW TO INSTALL/CONFIGURE IMPROJECT
DO REFER TO THE SECTION OF YOUR OS PLATFORM


-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
						WINDOWS PLATFORM
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The library is only configure to compile with a MinGW compiler.
No support is provided for other compilers.

1- Install CMake (binary distribution)
		http://www.cmake.org/cmake/resources/software.html
		Add the CMake bin directory to your path
2- Install LibJpeg, zlib with GnuWin32
		http://gnuwin32.sourceforge.net/packages.html
		Add the GnuWin32 bin directory to your path
3- Install GTKmm
		http://live.gnome.org/gtkmm/MSWindows
		Add the 
4- Install QT4 with MinGw included
		http://www.qtsoftware.com/downloads/opensource
		Add bin directories of MinGW and Qt to your PATH
5- Install Doxygen
		http://www.stack.nl/~dimitri/doxygen/
		Add bin directory of Doxygen to your PATH		

Note : If you prefer to use Dev-Cpp instead of a classical MinGW installation, 
simply add the bin directory to your PATH.
		
Open a shell (cmd.exe) and type 
cmake . -G "MinGW Makefiles"

To generate the makefiles, type make and this will build all the binairies.

Finally Add C:\...\IMProjectIMTiff\lib to your PATH.


-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
						UNIX AND APPLE PLATFORM
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Following libraries must be installed:

libtiff4-dev
libjpeg
libz
gettext
pkg-config
glib-2.0
libsigc++
glibmm-2.4
libxml-2
libxml++-2.6
cmake
doxygen

Build options

make debug : with debug info
make release : inline + O3
make interactive : interactive mode with ccmake
make clean : remove generated files
make cleanall : remove documentation

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
						ALL PLATFORMS
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
To regenerate documentation via doxygen, do
make








